WEBVTT

00:19.520 --> 00:20.100
1.

00:22.240 --> 00:27.940
For as much as many have taken in hand to set forth in order a declaration of those

00:27.940 --> 00:33.900
things which are most surely believed among us, even as they delivered them unto us, which

00:33.900 --> 00:40.500
from the beginning were eyewitnesses and ministers of the word, it seemed good to me also, having

00:40.500 --> 00:46.580
had perfect understanding of all things from the very first, to write unto thee in order,

00:46.800 --> 00:52.180
most excellent Theophilus, that thou mightest know the certainty of those things wherein

00:52.180 --> 00:53.760
thou hast been instructed.

00:54.620 --> 01:00.880
There was, in the days of Herod the king of Judea, a certain priest named Zacharias of

01:00.880 --> 01:05.700
the course of Abia, and his wife was of the daughters of Aaron, and her name was Elizabeth.

01:06.500 --> 01:12.120
And they were both righteous before God, walking in all the commandments and ordinances of

01:12.120 --> 01:13.400
the Lord blameless.

01:14.100 --> 01:20.140
And they had no child, because that Elizabeth was barren, and they both were now well stricken

01:20.140 --> 01:20.960
in years.

01:21.600 --> 01:27.680
And it came to pass, that while he executed the priest's office before God in the order

01:27.680 --> 01:33.180
of his course, according to the custom of the priest's office, his lot was to burn

01:33.180 --> 01:36.340
incense when he went into the temple of the Lord.

01:37.280 --> 01:41.580
And the whole multitude of the people were praying without at the time of incense.

01:42.640 --> 01:47.800
And there appeared unto him an angel of the Lord standing on the right side of the altar

01:47.800 --> 01:48.680
of incense.

01:49.400 --> 01:54.040
And when Zacharias saw him, he was troubled, and fear fell upon him.

01:54.720 --> 02:02.160
But the angel said unto him, Fear not, Zacharias, for thy prayer is heard, and thy wife Elizabeth

02:02.160 --> 02:06.480
shall bear thee a son, and thou shalt call his name John.

02:07.500 --> 02:12.400
And thou shalt have joy and gladness, and many shall rejoice at his birth.

02:13.020 --> 02:18.700
For he shall be great in the sight of the Lord, and shall drink neither wine nor strong

02:18.700 --> 02:23.760
drink, and he shall be filled with the Holy Ghost even from his mother's womb.

02:25.260 --> 02:29.260
And many of the children of Israel shall he turn to the Lord their God.

02:30.080 --> 02:35.820
And he shall go before him in the spirit and power of Elias to turn the hearts of the fathers

02:35.820 --> 02:41.560
to the children, and the disobedient to the wisdom of the just, to make ready a people

02:41.560 --> 02:43.180
prepared for the Lord.

02:44.180 --> 02:48.560
And Zacharias said unto the angel, Whereby shall I know this?

02:48.620 --> 02:52.660
For I am an old man, and my wife well stricken in years.

02:53.600 --> 03:00.700
And the angel answering said unto him, I am Gabriel, that stand in the presence of God,

03:01.040 --> 03:05.340
and am sent to speak unto thee, and to show thee these glad tidings.

03:06.880 --> 03:13.360
And behold, thou shalt be dumb, and not able to speak until the day that these things shall

03:13.360 --> 03:19.000
be performed, because thou believest not my words, which shall be fulfilled in their season.

03:19.800 --> 03:24.300
And the people waited for Zacharias, and marveled that he tarried so long in the temple.

03:25.260 --> 03:30.300
And when he came out, he could not speak unto them, and they perceived that he had seen

03:30.300 --> 03:34.980
a vision in the temple, for he beckoned unto them, and remained speechless.

03:35.700 --> 03:40.920
And it came to pass, that, as soon as the days of his ministration were accomplished,

03:41.200 --> 03:43.220
he departed to his own house.

03:43.760 --> 03:49.560
And after those days his wife Elizabeth conceived, and hid herself five months, saying, Thus

03:49.560 --> 03:54.640
hath the Lord dealt with me in the days wherein he looked on me, to take away my reproach

03:54.640 --> 03:55.480
among men.

03:56.200 --> 04:01.600
And in the sixth month the angel Gabriel was sent from God unto a city of Galilee,

04:01.920 --> 04:08.500
named Nazareth, to a virgin espoused to a man whose name was Joseph of the house of

04:08.500 --> 04:11.300
David, and the virgin's name was Mary.

04:12.140 --> 04:19.320
And the angel came in unto her, and said, Hail, thou that art highly favored, the Lord

04:19.320 --> 04:22.800
is with thee, blessed art thou among women.

04:23.700 --> 04:29.120
And when she saw him, she was troubled at his saying, and cast in her mind what manner

04:29.120 --> 04:31.120
of salutation this should be.

04:31.920 --> 04:37.960
And the angel said unto her, Fear not, Mary, for thou hast found favor with God.

04:38.700 --> 04:44.640
And behold, thou shalt conceive in thy womb, and bring forth a son, and shalt call his

04:44.640 --> 04:45.480
name Jesus.

04:46.120 --> 04:52.180
He shall be great, and shall be called the Son of the Highest, and the Lord God shall

04:52.180 --> 04:54.580
give unto him the throne of his father David.

04:55.200 --> 05:00.540
And he shall reign over the house of Jacob for ever, and of his kingdom there shall be

05:00.540 --> 05:01.300
no end.

05:02.420 --> 05:08.240
Then said Mary unto the angel, How shall this be, seeing I know not a man?

05:09.720 --> 05:15.560
And the angel answered and said unto her, The Holy Ghost shall come upon thee, and the

05:15.560 --> 05:17.840
power of the Highest shall overshadow thee.

05:17.840 --> 05:23.240
Therefore also that holy thing which shall be born of thee shall be called the Son of

05:23.240 --> 05:23.700
God.

05:24.600 --> 05:31.280
And behold, thy cousin Elizabeth, she hath also conceived a son in her old age, and this

05:31.280 --> 05:34.620
is the sixth month with her who was called barren.

05:35.040 --> 05:37.800
For with God nothing shall be impossible.

05:38.720 --> 05:44.480
And Mary said, Behold the handmaid of the Lord, be it unto me according to thy word.

05:44.880 --> 05:46.940
And the angel departed from her.

05:48.040 --> 05:52.520
And Mary arose in those days, and went into the hill country with haste, into a city of

05:52.520 --> 05:57.400
Judah, and entered into the house of Zacharias, and saluted Elizabeth.

05:58.140 --> 06:03.780
And it came to pass that when Elizabeth heard the salutation of Mary, the babe leaped in

06:03.780 --> 06:07.060
her womb, and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Ghost.

06:07.480 --> 06:14.060
And she spake out with a loud voice, and said, Blessed art thou among women, and blessed

06:14.060 --> 06:19.280
is the fruit of thy womb, and whence is this to me that the mother of my Lord should come

06:19.280 --> 06:19.900
to me?

06:20.300 --> 06:26.500
For lo, as soon as the voice of thy salutation sounded in mine ears, the babe leaped in my

06:26.500 --> 06:27.440
womb for joy.

06:28.160 --> 06:32.760
And blessed is she that believed, for thou shalt be a performance of those things which

06:32.760 --> 06:34.200
were told her from the Lord.

06:34.880 --> 06:42.300
And Mary said, My soul doth magnify the Lord, and my spirit hath rejoiced in God my Saviour.

06:42.300 --> 06:45.760
For he hath regarded the low estate of his handmaiden.

06:46.260 --> 06:50.980
For behold, from henceforth all generations shall call me blessed.

06:52.120 --> 06:58.200
For he that is mighty hath done to me great things, and holy is his name.

06:59.340 --> 07:03.760
And his mercy is on them that fear him from generation to generation.

07:04.240 --> 07:06.520
He hath shewed strength with his arm.

07:06.940 --> 07:10.740
He hath scattered the proud in the imagination of their hearts.

07:11.160 --> 07:16.880
He hath put down the mighty from their seats, and exalted them of low degree.

07:17.140 --> 07:22.660
He hath filled the hungry with good things, and the rich he hath sent empty away.

07:23.200 --> 07:28.560
He hath holpen his servant Israel in remembrance of his mercy, as he spake to our fathers,

07:28.880 --> 07:31.080
to Abraham, and to his seed for ever.

07:31.700 --> 07:35.780
And Mary abode with her about three months, and returned to her own house.

07:36.480 --> 07:41.720
Now Elizabeth's full time came that she should be delivered, and she brought forth a son.

07:42.240 --> 07:46.760
And her neighbors and her cousins heard how the Lord had showed great mercy upon her,

07:46.920 --> 07:48.700
and they rejoiced with her.

07:48.960 --> 07:54.540
And it came to pass that on the eighth day they came to circumcise the child, and they

07:54.540 --> 07:57.380
called him Zacharias after the name of his father.

07:58.260 --> 08:03.540
And his mother answered and said, Not so, but he shall be called John.

08:04.140 --> 08:08.100
And they said unto her, There is none of thy kindred that is called by this name.

08:08.620 --> 08:11.820
And they made signs to his father how he would have him called.

08:12.660 --> 08:17.260
And he asked for a writing table, and wrote, saying, His name is John.

08:17.700 --> 08:19.220
And they marveled all.

08:19.720 --> 08:24.060
And his mouth was opened immediately, and his tongue loosed, and he spake and praised

08:24.060 --> 08:24.500
God.

08:24.880 --> 08:30.080
And fear came on all that dwelt round about them, and all these sayings were noised abroad

08:30.080 --> 08:32.420
throughout all the hill country of Judea.

08:32.420 --> 08:37.620
And all they that heard them laid them up in their hearts, saying, What manner of child

08:37.620 --> 08:38.640
shall this be?

08:39.320 --> 08:41.220
And the hand of the Lord was with him.

08:41.660 --> 08:47.240
And his father Zacharias was filled with the Holy Ghost, and prophesied, saying, Blessed

08:47.240 --> 08:53.860
be the Lord God of Israel, for he hath visited and redeemed his people, and hath raised up

08:53.860 --> 08:59.080
an horn of salvation for us in the house of his servant David, as he spake by the mouth

08:59.080 --> 09:04.460
of his holy prophets, which have been since the world began, that we should be saved from

09:04.460 --> 09:09.420
our enemies, and from the hand of all that hate us, to perform the mercy promised to

09:09.420 --> 09:15.060
our fathers, and to remember his holy covenant, the oath which he sware to our father Abraham,

09:15.940 --> 09:21.520
that he would grant unto us, that we being delivered out of the hand of our enemies might

09:21.520 --> 09:28.000
serve him without fear, in holiness and righteousness before him all the days of our life.

09:28.640 --> 09:34.400
And thou, child, shalt be called the prophet of the highest, for thou shalt go before the

09:34.400 --> 09:40.240
face of the Lord to prepare his ways, to give knowledge of salvation unto his people by

09:40.240 --> 09:46.780
the remission of their sins, through the tender mercy of our God, whereby the day spring

09:46.780 --> 09:52.120
from on high hath visited us, to give light to them that sit in darkness and in the shadow

09:52.120 --> 09:55.720
of death, to guide our feet into the way of peace.

09:56.460 --> 10:02.580
And the child grew and waxed strong in spirit, and was in the deserts till the day of his

10:02.580 --> 10:04.280
showing unto Israel.

10:06.380 --> 10:07.580
CHAPTER II

10:07.580 --> 10:13.420
And it came to pass in those days, that there went out a decree from Caesar Augustus that

10:13.420 --> 10:15.540
all the world should be taxed.

10:15.760 --> 10:19.980
And this taxing was first made when Cyrenius was governor of Syria.

10:20.800 --> 10:24.760
And all went to be taxed, every one into his own city.

10:25.720 --> 10:31.720
And Joseph also went up from Galilee out of the city of Nazareth into Judea unto the city

10:31.720 --> 10:37.240
of David, which is called Bethlehem, because he was of the house and lineage of David,

10:37.760 --> 10:41.560
to be taxed with Mary his espoused wife being great with child.

10:42.300 --> 10:46.680
And so it was, that while they were there the days were accomplished that she should

10:47.420 --> 10:53.500
And she brought forth her firstborn son, and wrapped him in swaddling clothes, and laid

10:53.500 --> 10:57.180
him in a manger, because there was no room for them in the inn.

10:57.860 --> 11:02.780
And there were in the same country shepherds abiding in the field, keeping watch over

11:02.780 --> 11:04.000
their flock by night.

11:04.680 --> 11:05.340
And lo!

11:05.820 --> 11:10.960
the angel of the Lord came upon them, and the glory of the Lord shone round about them,

11:11.060 --> 11:12.740
and they were sore afraid.

11:13.600 --> 11:16.840
And the angel said unto them, Fear not!

11:17.320 --> 11:22.240
For behold, I bring you good tidings of great joy which shall be to all people.

11:22.920 --> 11:29.340
For unto you is born this day in the city of David a Saviour, which is Christ the Lord.

11:29.560 --> 11:32.000
And this shall be a sign unto you.

11:32.300 --> 11:36.080
Ye shall find the babe wrapped in swaddling clothes lying in a manger.

11:36.640 --> 11:42.720
And suddenly there was with the angel a multitude of the heavenly host, praising God and saying,

11:43.800 --> 11:49.000
Glory to God in the highest, and on earth peace, good will toward men.

11:50.160 --> 11:54.820
And it came to pass, as the angels were gone away from them into heaven, the shepherds

11:54.820 --> 12:00.460
said one to another, Let us now go even unto Bethlehem, and see this thing which is come

12:00.460 --> 12:04.000
to pass, which the Lord hath made known unto us.

12:04.660 --> 12:09.780
And they came with haste, and found Mary, and Joseph, and the babe lying in a manger.

12:10.700 --> 12:15.700
And when they had seen it, they made known abroad the saying which was told them concerning

12:15.700 --> 12:16.600
this child.

12:17.520 --> 12:22.040
And all they that heard it wondered at those things which were told them by the shepherds.

12:22.560 --> 12:26.320
But Mary kept all these things, and pondered them in her heart.

12:27.440 --> 12:32.040
And the shepherds returned, glorifying and praising God for all the things that they

12:32.040 --> 12:35.300
had heard and seen, as it was told unto them.

12:35.300 --> 12:40.200
And when eight days were accomplished for the circumcision of the child, his name was

12:40.200 --> 12:45.300
called Jesus, which was so named of the angel before he was conceived in the womb.

12:45.920 --> 12:50.980
And when the days of her purification according to the law of Moses were accomplished, they

12:50.980 --> 12:54.000
brought him to Jerusalem to present him to the Lord.

12:54.720 --> 13:00.760
As it is written in the law of the Lord, Every male that openeth the womb shall be called

13:00.760 --> 13:02.060
holy to the Lord.

13:02.740 --> 13:08.660
And to offer a sacrifice according to that which is said in the law of the Lord, a pair

13:08.660 --> 13:11.100
of turtle doves, or two young pigeons.

13:12.620 --> 13:16.600
And behold, there was a man in Jerusalem whose name was Simeon.

13:17.040 --> 13:22.700
And the same man was just and devout, waiting for the consolation of Israel.

13:23.040 --> 13:25.160
And the Holy Ghost was upon him.

13:25.460 --> 13:30.980
And it was revealed unto him by the Holy Ghost that he should not see death before he had

13:30.980 --> 13:32.460
seen the Lord's Christ.

13:33.000 --> 13:37.360
And he came by the Spirit into the temple, and when the parents brought in the child

13:37.360 --> 13:43.740
Jesus to do for him after the custom of the law, then took he him up in his arms and blessed

13:43.740 --> 13:44.960
God and said,

14:02.900 --> 14:07.480
And Joseph and his mother marveled at those things which were spoken of him.

14:08.020 --> 14:14.480
And Simeon blessed them, and said unto Mary his mother, Behold, this child is set for

14:14.480 --> 14:20.800
the fall and rising again of many in Israel, and for a sign which shall be spoken against.

14:21.520 --> 14:25.240
Yea, a sword shall pierce through thine own soul also.

14:25.240 --> 14:28.680
That the thoughts of many hearts may be revealed.

14:31.040 --> 14:36.700
And there was one Anna, a prophetess, the daughter of Phanuel, of the tribe of Aesir.

14:37.040 --> 14:42.240
She was of a great age, and had lived with a husband seven years from her virginity.

14:42.700 --> 14:47.980
And she was a widow of about four score and four years, which departed not from the temple

14:47.980 --> 14:51.560
but served God with fastings and prayers night and day.

14:52.340 --> 14:58.420
And she, coming in that instant, gave thanks likewise unto the Lord, and spake of him to

14:58.420 --> 15:01.140
all them that looked for redemption in Jerusalem.

15:01.720 --> 15:06.760
And when they had performed all things according to the law of the Lord, they returned into

15:06.760 --> 15:08.860
Galilee to their own city Nazareth.

15:09.600 --> 15:15.720
And the child grew and waxed strong in spirit, filled with wisdom, and the grace of God was

15:15.720 --> 15:16.480
upon him.

15:17.260 --> 15:20.980
Now his parents went to Jerusalem every year at the feast of the Passover.

15:21.680 --> 15:26.540
And when he was twelve years old, they went up to Jerusalem after the custom of the feast.

15:27.180 --> 15:32.680
And when they had fulfilled the days, as they returned, the child Jesus tarried behind in

15:32.680 --> 15:36.140
Jerusalem, and Joseph and his mother knew not of it.

15:37.080 --> 15:42.840
But they, supposing him to have been in the company, went a day's journey, and they sought

15:42.840 --> 15:45.260
him among their kinsfolk and acquaintance.

15:45.260 --> 15:49.820
And when they found him not, they turned back again to Jerusalem, seeking him.

15:50.400 --> 15:55.040
And it came to pass that after three days they found him in the temple, sitting in the

15:55.040 --> 15:59.500
midst of the doctors, both hearing them and asking them questions.

16:00.040 --> 16:04.460
And all that heard him were astonished at his understanding and answers.

16:05.440 --> 16:07.360
And when they saw him, they were amazed.

16:07.720 --> 16:12.780
And his mother said unto him, Son, why hast thou thus dealt with us?

16:12.780 --> 16:16.380
Behold, thy father and I have sought thee sorrowing.

16:16.820 --> 16:20.880
And he said unto them, How is it that ye sought me?

16:21.500 --> 16:24.740
Wisst ye not that I must be about my father's business?

16:25.540 --> 16:28.920
And they understood not the saying which he spake unto them.

16:29.100 --> 16:33.020
And he went down with them and came to Nazareth, and was subject unto them.

16:33.300 --> 16:36.100
But his mother kept all these sayings in her heart.

16:36.720 --> 16:42.320
And Jesus increased in wisdom and stature, and in favor with God and man.

16:43.780 --> 16:45.620
End of chapters 1 and 2.

